messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 11/24/02 8:55:44 AM Central Standard Time,
Unschooling-dotcom@yahoogroups.com writes:

<< Hope someone can
help us. >>

Well, that's not nearly enough information to go on. My first thought was
some type of Grosbeak, but I'd need a lot more descriptive info. as what you
put could fit probably a hundred or so birds.
Where do you live?
Did you see it recently?
Birding can be a lot of fun, but frustrating too! I recommend that you buy a
Petersons guide and/or the audobon field guides for birds in your area.

Ren
"The answers aren't important really...
What's important, is knowing all the questions."
-Zilpha Keatley Snyder
